= Personal Interests  

== Future City Competition 
For the last three years I have been a Special Award Judge, from IEEE Chicago, to [http://futurecity.org/ Future City Competition].  Future City is a competition for 6th, 7th, and 8th graders where students design their vision of a future city with simulation software, build scale models, write essays, and give oral presentations.

-  Future City 2016  Competition pictures are available at [https://goo.gl/Yf0T4X Flickr.]
-  Future City 2015 Competition IEEE Report is available at  [http://ieeechicago.org/2015/02/10/future-city-report-for-2015/ IEEE.] 
- Future City 2015  Competition pictures are available at [https://goo.gl/W6Xcib Flickr.]
- Future City 2014  Competition pictures are available at [https://goo.gl/t32Ols Flickr.]

== Books 
Reading Books is one of my passions.  Here is a short list of my favorite  modern fiction and non-fiction writers:

. English Language:  
 .. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malcolm_Gladwell Malcolm Gladwell. ] I recommend all of his books. My personal favorite is "Outliers." He also has a number of very interesting [https://www.ted.com/talks/malcolm_gladwell_the_unheard_story_of_david_and_goliath?language=en TED talks.] 
 .. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jared_Diamond Jared Diamond. ] "Guns, Germs and Steel" has been one my favorite books since high school.
 .. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simon_Singh Simon Singh.] I would like to thank [https://ece.uic.edu/profiles/vladimir-goncharoff-phd/ Dr. Goncharoff] for gifting to me a copy of [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fermat%27s_Last_Theorem_(book) Fermat's Last Theorem.]
 . Ukrainian Language: 
 .. [https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%A1%D0%BA%D0%BB%D1%8F%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BA%D0%BE_%D0%A1%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B5%D0%BD_%D0%94%D0%BC%D0%B8%D1%82%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%87 Semen Skliarenko (Ukrainian: Скляренко Семен Дмитрович).] My favorite is  a historic novel [https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%92%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B8%D0%BC%D0%B8%D1%80_(%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B0%D0%BD) Volodymyr (Ukranian: Володимир)]  about prince of Kievan Rus.'  Unfortunately, the novel has not been translated yet.
 . Russian Language: 
 ..  [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Akunin Boris Akunin (Russian: Борис Акунин).] One of my favorite modern Russian writers. His series on 19th century detective Erast Fandorin (Russian: Эраст Петрович Фандорин)  is one my favorite. For those interested, many of his books are available in translation.

 *Currently Reading:* Bosch and Schelm (Russian: Бох и Шельма) by Boris Akunin. Unfortunately, I do not think the book has been translated to English yet.




